<li id="cite_note-4"><b><a href="#cite_ref-4" title="">^</a></b> Antoine Guillaumont reports the finding of an inscription containing the Jesus Prayer in the ruins of a cell in the Egyptian desert dated roughly to the period being discussed - Antoine Guillaumont, <i>Une inscription copte sur la prière de Jesus</i> in <i>Aux origines du monachisme chrétien, Pour une phénoménologie du monachisme</i>, pp. 168–83. In <i>Spiritualité orientale et vie monastique</i>, No 30. Bégrolles en Mauges (Maine &amp; Loire), France: Abbaye de Bellefontaine.</li>
<li id="cite_note-panagiotis-ro-5">^ <a href="#cite_ref-panagiotis-ro_5-0" title=""><sup><i><b>a</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-panagiotis-ro_5-1" title=""><sup><i><b>b</b></i></sup></a> <a href="#cite_ref-panagiotis-ro_5-2" title=""><sup><i><b>c</b></i></sup></a> <span class="languageicon" style="font-size:0.95em; font-weight:bold; color:#555;">(Romanian)</span> Christopher Panagiotis, <i>Rugăciunea lui Iisus. Unirea minţii cu inima şi a omului cu Dumnezeu</i> (<i>Jesus prayer. Uniting the mind with the heart and man with God</i>), translation from <a href="/wiki/Greek_language" title="Greek language">Greek</a>, 2nd edition, Panaghia Ed., Rarău Monastery, <a href="/wiki/Vatra_Dornei" title="Vatra Dornei">Vatra Dornei</a>, pp. 6, 12-15, 130, <a href="/wiki/Special:BookSources/9789738821866" class="internal">ISBN 978-973-88218-6-6</a>.</li>
